The shutil (shell utilities) module is used for:
File copy
Directory copy
Removing files/folders
Moving/renaming files
Archiving (zip, tar)
Checking disk usage
High-level file operations
Itâ€™s basically a Swiss-army knife for file management in Python!

â­ 1. Importing the module
import shutil

â­ 2. Copy a File
ğŸ“Œ shutil.copy()
Copies file with content but not file permissions.
import shutil
shutil.copy("source.txt", "backup.txt")
print("File copied!")

â­ 3. Copy a File With Permissions
ğŸ“Œ shutil.copy2()
Copies file with metadata (permissions, timestamps).
shutil.copy2("source.txt", "backup_with_permissions.txt")

â­ 4. Copy Entire Folder (directory)
ğŸ“Œ shutil.copytree()
shutil.copytree("myfolder", "myfolder_backup")

This will duplicate the whole directory.

â­ 5. Move or Rename Files/Folders
ğŸ“Œ shutil.move()
shutil.move("old_folder", "new_folder")

Same function works for renaming:
shutil.move("file1.txt", "file2.txt")

â­ 6. Delete Folder
ğŸ“Œ shutil.rmtree()
(Removes directory recursively â€” Be careful!)
shutil.rmtree("temp_folder")

â­ 7. Create ZIP/TAR Archive
ğŸ“Œ shutil.make_archive()
shutil.make_archive("project_backup", "zip", "project_folder")

This creates:
project_backup.zip

â­ 8. Extract ZIP/TAR Archives
ğŸ“Œ shutil.unpack_archive()
shutil.unpack_archive("project_backup.zip", "restore_here")

â­ 9. Check Disk Usage
ğŸ“Œ shutil.disk_usage()
usage = shutil.disk_usage("/")
print("Total:", usage.total)
print("Used:", usage.used)
print("Free:", usage.free)

Amazing for system-admin tasks!

â­ 10. Which Program Path?
ğŸ“Œ shutil.which()
Finds full path of a command (like which in Linux):
print(shutil.which("python3"))
print(shutil.which("kubectl"))

Very useful in DevOps automation!

ğŸ¯ Complete Practical Example
Letâ€™s combine everything:
import shutil
# Copy file
shutil.copy("config.yaml", "config_backup.yaml")
# Copy directory
shutil.copytree("/etc/nginx", "/tmp/nginx_backup")
# Move log file
shutil.move("/var/log/app.log", "/backup/app.log")
# Archive directory
shutil.make_archive("nginx_archive", "zip", "/etc/nginx")
# Check disk usage
usage = shutil.disk_usage("/")
print(f"Free space: {usage.free / (1024**3):.2f} GB")
